Ukraine’s Gross Foreign Debt Increased on Bond Sale, Hryvnia

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-09-16T16:17:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/ukraine-s-gross-foreign-debt-increased-on-bond-sale-hryvnia.html
Ukraine’s gross external debt rose
5.1 percent in the first half of the year after a Eurobond sale
and on a weaker hryvnia, the central bank said.  Debt totaled $123.4 billion as of July 1, compared with
$117.3 billion at the beginning of the year, the Kiev-based
 Natsionalnyi Bank Ukrainy  said today in a statement on its
website.  The government’s foreign debt rose to $27.3 billion from
$24.9 billion on Jan. 1, the bank said.  Foreign borrowing by the Ukrainian banks declined to $27.5
billion from $28.1 billion at the beginning of the year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 